        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> closes #29792 ?\r\n\r\nActually I don't think it does, and I think I made a mistake by commenting there. Apologies for that.\r\n\r\n#29792 is about only pulling diagnostics on save, rather than on every didChange. This PR only fixes a bug that caused didChange to be delayed and thus diagnostics to also be delayed — potentially a long time after the save.\r\n\r\nOnly pulling diagnostics on save is an alternative to having a high debounce - one which might not be very useful as many language servers spend their CPU cycles on didChange anyway.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-20T08:59:19Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39894#issuecomment-4496477868",
